Supported parameters:

-h --help --- shows help
-v --version --- shows version of Stepper
-q --quest "<quest_name>" --- sets name of quest to be loaded
-d --quests-dir "<quests_dir>" --- sets directory (relative to work. dir.) where the data of the quests lies

For example: this command, runs quest "Lone Island" (all spaces are replaced with underscores and name is got in lower case) from folder "quests" relate to working directory:
--quests-dir "quests" --quest "Lone island"

--qeust-dir and --quest are mandatory parameters.
